# Decision Layer — Frozen

These files are the **frozen v1 decision contract surface** (master plan §6 + invariant #11). New orchestration semantics belong in the commitment kernel, not here.

## What is frozen

The five legacy contracts and their immediate classifier / registry surface:

- `TaskContract`, `OutcomeContract`, `QualificationExecutionContract` (in `contracts.ts` and adjacent)
- `ResolutionContract` (in `resolution-contract.ts`)
- `RecipeRoutingHints`
- Plus `task-classifier.ts`, `tool-registry.ts`, `input.ts` as the decision orchestration entry surface.

`src/platform/decision/trace.ts` is **not** in this rule's globs — it has a sanctioned commitment/ extension point, see PR-1 sub-plan §4.

## What is allowed without label

- Pure bug-fix that clearly does not change routing semantics.
- Telemetry / logging additions.
- Refactor that preserves all observable behavior (must include bit-identical decision-eval snapshot proof).

## What requires the labeled PR template

Any new orchestration-semantics field, any new outcome enum value, any new phrase / keyword routing patch:

- [ ] telemetry-only
- [ ] bug-fix
- [ ] compatibility (REQUIRES `source-of-truth: ExecutionCommitment.<...>` declared in PR description)
- [ ] emergency-rollback (REQUIRES tracking ticket + retire deadline)

If a request comes to add a new outcome, a new phrase guard, a new variant kind, a new "deliverable" field — **STOP**. New orchestration semantics belong in the commitment kernel. Surface to the user before any code change.

Master plan: `.cursor/plans/commitment_kernel_v1_master.plan.md` §6 "Five-Layer Freeze"
